{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "# Tips\n",
    "\n",
    "Click the button below to run this notebook directly on Google Colab:\n",
    "\n",
    "[<img src=\"https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg\" align=\"left\">](https://colab.research.google.com/github)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Introduction:\n",
    "\n",
    "This exercise was created based on the tutorial and documentation from [Seaborn](https://stanford.edu/~mwaskom/software/seaborn/index.html)  \n",
    "The dataset being used is tips from Seaborn.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Step 1. Import the necessary libraries:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "%matplotlib inline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 2. Import the dataset from this [address](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/thieu1995/csv-files/main/data/pandas/tips.csv)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 3. Assign it to a variable called tips"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "url = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/thieu1995/csv-files/main/data/pandas/tips.csv'\n",
    "tips = pd.read_csv(url)\n",
    "if 'Unnamed: 0' in tips.columns:\n",
    "    tips = tips.drop(columns=['Unnamed: 0'])\n",
    "tips.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 4. Delete the Unnamed 0 column"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Column deleted during step 3 assignment if present\n",
    "tips.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 5. Plot the total_bill column histogram"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ttbill = sns.histplot(tips.total_bill, kde=True)\n",
    "ttbill.set(xlabel='Value', ylabel='Frequency', title='Total Bill')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 6. Create a scatter plot presenting the relationship between total_bill and tip"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sns.jointplot(x='total_bill', y='tip', data=tips)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 7.  Create one image with the relationship of total_bill, tip and size."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sns.pairplot(tips)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 8. Present the relationship between days and total_bill value"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sns.stripplot(x='day', y='total_bill', data=tips, jitter=True)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 9. Create a scatter plot with the day as the y-axis and tip as the x-axis, differ the dots by sex"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sns.stripplot(x='tip', y='day', hue='sex', data=tips, jitter=True)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 10.  Create a box plot presenting the total_bill per day differencing the time (Dinner or Lunch)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sns.boxplot(x='day', y='total_bill', hue='time', data=tips)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 11. Create two histograms of the tip value based on Dinner and Lunch time, seductive side by side"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "g = sns.FacetGrid(tips, col='time')\n",
    "g.map(sns.histplot, 'tip')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 12. Create two scatterplots graphs, one for Male and another for Female, presenting the total_bill value and tip relationship, differing by smoker or no smoker\n",
    "### They must be side by side."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "g = sns.FacetGrid(tips, col='sex', hue='smoker')\n",
    "g.map(sns.scatterplot, 'total_bill', 'tip')\n",
    "g.add_legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### BONUS: Create your own question and answer it using a graph."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Question: What is the average tip amount for each day of the week, broken down by gender?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,\n    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sns.barplot(x='day', y='tip', hue='sex', data=tips, errorbar=None)\n",
    "plt.title('Average Tip by Day and Gender')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
 ],
